    <h1>Development tools</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>The tools used for development are&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li>Confluence (Documentation, this same tool)</li>
<li><a rel=3D"nofollow" class=3D"external-link" href=3D"https://jira.iais.f=
raunhofer.de/jira/projects/GEC/summary">JIRA</a>&nbsp;(Project Management)<=
/li>
<li><a class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow" href=3D"https://jira.iais.f=
raunhofer.de/stash/projects/GEC">Bitbucket</a>&nbsp;(Source code repositori=
es)</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://dtr.iais.fraunhofer.de/" class=3D"external-link" rel=
=3D"nofollow">Sonarqube</a> (Code Quality check)&nbsp;</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://jira.iais.fraunhofer.de/bamboo/browse/EISGEC" class=
=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Bamboo</a> (Build and Continuous integr=
ation server)</li>
<li><a class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow" href=3D"https://mvn.isst.fr=
aunhofer.de/nexus">Nexus</a>&nbsp;(ISST Maven artifacts repository)</li>
<li><a href=3D"http://maven.iais.fraunhofer.de/" class=3D"external-link" re=
l=3D"nofollow">Artifactory</a> (IAIS Maven artifacts repository)</li>
<li><a href=3D"https://gitlab.cc-asp.fraunhofer.de/lselmi/gec/container_reg=
istry" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Docker registry</a>&nbsp;(d=
ocker images)</li>
</ul>
<h1 id=3D"Developmenttools-JIRA">JIRA</h1>
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"Developmenttools-Bitbucket">Bitbucket</h1>
<p>Bitbucket is the source version control system. It uses the git protocol=
 so there is no difference in using Bitbucket or Github. The GEC project ha=
s its own project on Bitbucket, <a href=3D"https://jira.iais.fraunhofer.de/=
stash/projects/GEC" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">German Edge Cl=
oud</a>, where software repositories can be created.&nbsp;</p>
<h1 id=3D"Developmenttools-Sonarqube">Sonarqube</h1>
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"Developmenttools-Bamboo">Bamboo</h1>
<p>Bamboo is used to execute the unit tests, compile the source code, and b=
uild the artifacts (e.g. .jar files) from the source code. Bamboo must know=
 where the source code is (i.e. the Bitbucket repository), which build fram=
ework and command have to be used (e.g. Maven 3.0 with "clean package" as g=
oal) in order to compile the software, and finally which type of artifacts =
have to be created (e.g. a Java .jar file). The artifacts created can be de=
ployed on a server for the integration tests. In order to configure Bamboo =
to build and create artifacts from a repository you have follow these steps=
</p>
<ol>
<li>Create a project</li>
<li>Create a plan</li>
<li>Add the source code repository to the plan</li>
<li>Define the trigger to start the plan</li>
<li>Define the artifacts to be created after the plan is executed</li>
<li>Add a "Checkout Source Code" task to the plan</li>
<li>Add a "Maven 3.0" task to the plan&nbsp;</li>
</ol>
<p>Usually only the Atlassian servers admin can create a project on Bamboo.=
 You can test your plan running it from Bamboo. You can also check the trig=
ger by pushing a change to the Bitbucket repository linked to the plan. The=
 documentation on how to create projects and plans is available from the At=
lassian website for <a href=3D"https://confluence.atlassian.com/bamboo/unde=
rstanding-the-bamboo-ci-server-289277285.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=
=3D"nofollow">Bamboo</a>.</p>
<h1 id=3D"Developmenttools-Nexus">Nexus</h1>
<p><br></p>
<h1 id=3D"Developmenttools-Dockerregistry">Docker registry</h1>
<p>Fraunhofer provides a&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://info.fraunhofer.de/it/web-=
server-daten/GitLab/Seiten/default.aspx" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nof=
ollow">docker container registry</a>&nbsp;where docker images can be pushed=
 and pulled out. This mechanism allows a faster deployment of components be=
cause there will be no need to build the software or the image of the compo=
nent on the machine where the component has to be deployed. The image will =
be build by Bamboo and pushed to the container registry where it can be pul=
led and deployed on any server where a docker engine is installed. In order=
 to <a href=3D"https://gitlab.cc-asp.fraunhofer.de/users/sign_in" class=3D"=
external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">sign-in in the docker registry</a> a user m=
ust use her Fraunhofer-UserID that is available in the Self-Service tab of =
the <a href=3D"https://www.directory.fraunhofer.de/" class=3D"external-link=
" rel=3D"nofollow">Fraunhofer directory</a>&nbsp;(you need to log-in with t=
he SmartCard to see the tab) together with her Fraunhofer password. Additio=
nal information about the Fraunhofer Container Registry can be found <a hre=
f=3D"https://jira.iais.fraunhofer.de/wiki/display/ATLASSIAN/Bamboo-Builds+u=
nd+Fraunhofer+Docker+Registry#space-menu-link-content" rel=3D"nofollow">her=
e</a>&nbsp;and <a href=3D"https://jira.iais.fraunhofer.de/wiki/display/ATLA=
SSIAN/Docker" rel=3D"nofollow">here</a>.</p>
<h2 id=3D"Developmenttools-ExampleofUsingDockerRegistryforPushingandPulling=
DockerImages"><span style=3D"color: rgb(0,51,102);">Example of Using Docker=
 Registry for Pushing and Pulling Docker Images</span></h2>
<pre>The registry can be found here. The second username(the one for eduroa=
m) and primary password(the one for mailbox) are needed to login.<br>Use th=
e following command to login the registry:<br>docker login <a href=3D"http:=
//registry.gitlab.cc-asp.fraunhofer.de" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofo=
llow">registry.gitlab.cc-asp.fraunhofer.de</a>:4567<br><br>Then go to the f=
older with Dockerfile you want to build and Use the command to build the im=
age (connector-core for example):<br>docker build -t <a href=3D"http://regi=
stry.gitlab.cc-asp.fraunhofer.de" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">=
registry.gitlab.cc-asp.fraunhofer.de</a>:4567/lselmi/gec/connector-core .<b=
r><br>Use the following command to push the image to registry:<br>docker pu=
sh <a href=3D"http://registry.gitlab.cc-asp.fraunhofer.de" class=3D"externa=
l-link" rel=3D"nofollow">registry.gitlab.cc-asp.fraunhofer.de</a>:4567/lsel=
mi/gec/connector-core<br><br>And use the command to pull the image (have to=
 login the registry first): <br>docker pull <a href=3D"http://registry.gitl=
ab.cc-asp.fraunhofer.de" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">registry.=
gitlab.cc-asp.fraunhofer.de</a>:4567/lselmi/gec/connector-core</pre>
